At JRLA, we are focused on developing leaders for our school, our community, and the world. We know our scholars can do amazing things when given the chance.

This year, a new elective - Advanced Leadership Program - is amplifying scholars‚Äô voices by giving them direct leadership roles in the systems and policies at JRLA. This course is open to ALL scholars, 9-12, regardless of prior academic GPA or discipline data!

Want more information? There will be another information session this Wednesday, 9/2, from 4:30-5:30.

Respond to this post by DM or by emailing Mr. Harzula (harzular@jrladetroit.com) if you‚Äôre interested.

Information regarding arrangements will be shared as they become available.

post_text:
Every other Wednesday, #JRLA scholars attend Math Circles at U of M-Dearborn. Here's a few snaps of them completing their team activities.

The task was Toads and Frogs <https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Toads_and_Frogs>. We started with the 1-dimensional instance shown in the Wikipedia article as a warm-up for the 2D version: <https://www.cut-the-knot.org/SimpleGames/FrogsAndToads2D.shtml>.
Our newest member Dorien Johnson was the first to solve the 5x5 example. Many scholars pursued the extension to a 7x7 board. I think all of our scholars at JRLA would benefit from exposure to tasks like this one.
